cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a novel hybrid analog-digital architecture for millimeter-wave massive MIMO systems, which involves designing a digital precoder with tunable peak-to-average power ratio (PAPR) to improve system performance. This involves information theory concepts such as channel coding and modulation. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with millimeter-wave massive MIMO systems, which are used for high-speed data transmission in multimedia applications. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper proposes a novel hybrid analog-digital architecture for millimeter-wave massive MIMO systems, which involves designing a digital precoder to improve system performance. This involves signal processing techniques such as filtering and equalization. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with millimeter-wave massive MIMO systems, which are used for high-speed data transmission in wireless networks. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes a novel hybrid analog-digital architecture for millimeter-wave massive MIMO systems, which involves designing a passive reflect- or transmit-array for the analog front-end to improve scalability and reduce implementational costs. This involves hardware architecture concepts such as antenna design and implementation.
